T*
T*
(JARVIS USER MANUAL) Tj
T*
T*
T*
T*
(1. WHAT JARVIS IS) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(JARVIS is a local assistant built on OpenJarvis with:) Tj
T*
T*
(? a sci-fi HUD operator interface) Tj
T*
(? Norwegian and English voice input) Tj
T*
(? English-only replies) Tj
T*
(? approval-based actions) Tj
T*
(? desktop, coding, document, visual, and mission workflows) Tj
T*
T*
(The current product has two main ways to run:) Tj
T*
T*
(? Desktop app: the preferred app-like experience) Tj
T*
(? Web HUD: the fallback and development-friendly experience) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(2. RECOMMENDED WAY TO START JARVIS) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(### Preferred local launch) Tj
T*
T*
(From the repo root:) Tj
T*
T*
T*
([Code]) Tj
T*
(    .\\start_openjarvis.ps1) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Or:) Tj
T*
T*
T*
([Code]) Tj
T*
(    C:\\Users\\hogne\\OpenJarvis\\start_openjarvis.bat) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(The launcher now gives you these choices:) Tj
T*
T*
(1. Start desktop app) Tj
T*
(2. Start web HUD in Ubuntu) Tj
T*
(3. Check Windows desktop readiness) Tj
T*
(4. Collect desktop report) Tj
T*
T*
(### Best choice for normal use) Tj
T*
T*
(Choose `1` to start the desktop app.) Tj
T*
T*
(That launches the active Tauri shell in `frontend/src-tauri`, boots the local runtime,) Tj
T*
(and opens the JARVIS HUD with desktop lifecycle controls.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(3. STARTUP PROCEDURE) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(Root cause of earlier startup pain was that JARVIS could launch processes without) Tj
T*
(verifying that voice and runtime dependencies were actually ready. The current startup) Tj
T*
1 0 0 1 54 24 Tm
/F1 9 Tf
(JARVIS User Manual   Page 1 of 8) Tj
ET
endstream
