(flow now checks:) Tj
T*
T*
(? runtime readiness) Tj
T*
(? speech backend availability) Tj
T*
(? voice loop state) Tj
T*
(? core app dependencies) Tj
T*
T*
(### What you should expect) Tj
T*
T*
(On launch, JARVIS should:) Tj
T*
T*
(1. open the setup/startup screen) Tj
T*
(2. check inference, model, and API readiness) Tj
T*
(3. arm the voice loop when possible) Tj
T*
(4. open the HUD once the system is usable) Tj
T*
T*
(If something is blocked, JARVIS should surface that clearly instead of failing silently.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(4. MAIN PAGES) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(JARVIS is no longer supposed to keep everything on one dashboard. The main pages are:) Tj
T*
T*
(### Dashboard) Tj
T*
T*
(The command-center view for the most important live information.) Tj
T*
T*
(Use it for:) Tj
T*
T*
(? mission overview) Tj
T*
(? quick operator awareness) Tj
T*
(? command and approval flow) Tj
T*
(? high-priority assistant activity) Tj
T*
T*
(### Workspace) Tj
T*
T*
(Use this for:) Tj
T*
T*
(? repo and coding work) Tj
T*
(? self-improve workflows) Tj
T*
(? FiveM and Lua coding lanes) Tj
T*
(? workbench-oriented tasks) Tj
T*
T*
(### Briefings) Tj
T*
T*
(Use this for:) Tj
T*
T*
(? visual briefs) Tj
T*
(? document briefs) Tj
T*
(? design briefs) Tj
T*
(? saved and routed brief-style work) Tj
T*
T*
(### Operations) Tj
T*
T*
(Use this for:) Tj
T*
T*
