T*
T*
(### Show Window / Hide To Tray) Tj
T*
T*
(Closing the window should hide JARVIS to the tray rather than killing the session. Use) Tj
T*
(the page or tray menu when you want to bring it back.) Tj
T*
T*
(### Prepare Shutdown) Tj
T*
T*
(Use when you want a cleaner stand-down:) Tj
T*
T*
(1. stop voice activity) Tj
T*
(2. stop runtime) Tj
T*
(3. then quit) Tj
T*
T*
(### Quit Desktop App) Tj
T*
T*
(Use this when you want JARVIS fully closed.) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(9. WEB HUD FALLBACK) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(If the desktop build path is unavailable or Windows desktop packaging is blocked, use:) Tj
T*
T*
T*
([Code]) Tj
T*
(    .\\start_openjarvis_web.ps1) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This remains a valid fallback for:) Tj
T*
T*
(? frontend work) Tj
T*
(? browser-based usage) Tj
T*
(? development) Tj
T*
(? situations where native packaging is blocked by policy) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(10. CODING WORK) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(JARVIS includes a strong coding/operator workflow with:) Tj
T*
T*
(? repo awareness) Tj
T*
(? review queue) Tj
T*
(? self-improve missions) Tj
T*
(? direct file editing flows) Tj
T*
(? validation loops) Tj
T*
(? FiveM and Lua coding intelligence) Tj
T*
T*
(### For coding work) Tj
T*
T*
(Go to `Workspace`.) Tj
T*
T*
(That is the better place for:) Tj
T*
T*
(? repo operations) Tj
T*
(? coding missions) Tj
T*
